content.problemStatement:
In the last two lessons we learned how to print outputs on multiple lines and how to print text and numbers together.

To print output on multiple lines, we use **endl**.
```cpp
cout << 20 << endl;
cout << 2 + 2 << endl;

// Output:
// 20
// 4
```

To print text and number together we can put all of that in a single cout statement:
```cpp
cout << "This is lesson " << 3 << " of C++" << endl;

// Output:
// This is lesson 3 of C++
```

Let us solve a few more problems and then we will understand the structure of C++ code.

